ExecDesc.value: Oracle Outside In CorelDRAW File Parser Stack Buffer Overflow

EngDesc.value: A stack buffer overflow vulnerability exists in Oracle Outside-In, a set of libraries used to decode many file formats. The vulnerability exists when handling CorelDRAW (.cdr) files. Oracle Outside-In is embedded in many enterprise applications. This vulnerability can be exploited by causing an application that uses the vulnerable library to handle a malformed .cdr file. Depending on the application, user interaction may be required. Successful exploitation can result in arbitrary code execution in the context of the affected application.
